---
// DFIR Regex Tester & Pattern Library — live regex evaluation against pasted
// sample text, with inline match highlighting and a capture-group
// breakdown, plus a library of common DFIR-relevant patterns. Same page
// shape as the Hash Calculator / IOC Extractor (intro aside -> interactive
// tool -> reference notes). Static page — prerender to HTML served from the CDN.
export const prerender = true;
import { css } from 'styled-system/css';
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../../components/PageHeader.astro';
import Icon from '../../components/Icon.astro';
import RegexTester from '../../components/RegexTester.astro';
import Term from '../../components/Term.astro';
import { toolChip } from '../../components/RelatedTools.astro';
import { DFIR_REGEX_PATTERNS } from '../../utils/regexPatterns';

const sectionH2 = css({
  display: 'flex',
  alignItems: 'center',
  gap: '0.6rem',
  fontSize: '1.3rem',
  fontWeight: 700,
  mt: '2.5rem',
  mb: '1rem',
  pt: '1.5rem',
  borderTop: '1px solid token(colors.border)',
  scrollMarginTop: '90px',
});
const refTable = css({ width: '100%', borderCollapse: 'collapse', fontSize: '0.85rem' });
const refTh = css({ textAlign: 'left', color: 'textMuted', fontFamily: 'sans', fontWeight: 600, fontSize: '0.72rem', textTransform: 'uppercase', letterSpacing: '0.06em', p: '0.5rem 0.7rem', borderBottom: '1px solid token(colors.border)' });
const refTd = css({ p: '0.5rem 0.7rem', borderBottom: '1px solid token(colors.border)', color: 'text', verticalAlign: 'top' });
const refTdMuted = css({ p: '0.5rem 0.7rem', borderBottom: '1px solid token(colors.border)', color: 'textMuted', fontSize: '0.8rem', verticalAlign: 'top' });
const refCode = css({ fontFamily: 'mono', fontSize: '0.78rem', color: 'primary', wordBreak: 'break-word' });
const relatedList = css({ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', gap: '0.85rem' });
const relatedReason = css({ color: 'textMuted', fontSize: '0.85rem', mt: '0.35rem', lineHeight: 1.6 });
---

<BaseLayout
  title="DFIR Regex Tester & Pattern Library"
  description="Live regex playground with inline match highlighting, a capture-group breakdown, and a library of common DFIR patterns — IPv4/IPv6, Windows SIDs, GUIDs, file paths, registry keys, and more — entirely in your browser."
>
  <PageHeader
    breadcrumbs={[{ label: 'Home', href: '/' }, { label: 'Tool Catalog', href: '/tools/' }, { label: 'Regex Tester' }]}
    eyebrow="Triage & Correlation"
    title="DFIR Regex Tester & Pattern Library"
    description="Test a pattern against sample text with live match highlighting and a capture-group breakdown, or start from a library of common DFIR patterns."
  />

  <aside
    class={css({
      bg: 'bgSubtle',
      border: '1px solid token(colors.border)',
      borderLeftWidth: '3px',
      borderLeftColor: 'primary',
      borderRadius: 'md',
      p: '1rem 1.25rem',
      mb: '1.5rem',
    })}
  >
    <p class={css({ color: 'text', lineHeight: 1.7, fontSize: '0.95rem', m: 0 })}>
      Everything here runs entirely in your browser — <strong class={css({ color: 'text' })}>no external APIs, no
      upload, nothing you type or paste ever leaves your machine</strong>. The pattern, flags, and sample text are
      evaluated locally with JavaScript's own regex engine as you type.
    </p>
  </aside>

  <p class={css({ color: 'text', lineHeight: 1.8, fontSize: '1rem', mb: '1.5rem' })}>
    A regex tester earns its keep in two very different DFIR moments: hunting a raw log dump or console-output
    paste for anything matching a known shape — an internal IP range, a suspicious registry key pattern, a GUID
    that keeps recurring — before reaching for a dedicated extractor; and validating a pattern before it ships in
    a detection rule. That second use case isn't a coincidence: a <Term slug="sigma-rule">Sigma rule</Term>'s{' '}
    <code class={css({ fontFamily: 'mono', fontSize: '0.9rem', color: 'primary' })}>|re</code> modifier is
    evaluated with JavaScript's own <code class={css({ fontFamily: 'mono', fontSize: '0.9rem', color: 'primary' })}>RegExp</code>{' '}
    engine here too (see the Sigma Rule Tester), so a pattern you get working in this tester will behave
    identically once it's pasted into a rule's <code class={css({ fontFamily: 'mono', fontSize: '0.9rem', color: 'primary' })}>|re</code> field.
  </p>

  <h2 id="tester" class={css({ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '0.6rem', fontSize: '1.3rem', fontWeight: 700, mb: '1rem', scrollMarginTop: '90px' })}>
    <Icon name="search" size={20} class={css({ color: 'primary' })} /> Tester
  </h2>
  <RegexTester />

  <h2 id="reference" class={sectionH2}>
    <Icon name="list" size={20} class={css({ color: 'primary' })} /> Pattern library reference
  </h2>
  <div class={css({ overflowX: 'auto' })}>
    <table class={refTable}>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th class={refTh}>Pattern</th>
          <th class={refTh}>Regex</th>
          <th class={refTh}>Flags</th>
          <th class={refTh}>Notes</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {
          DFIR_REGEX_PATTERNS.map((p) => (
            <tr>
              <td class={refTd}>
                <strong class={css({ color: 'text' })}>{p.label}</strong>
              </td>
              <td class={refTd}>
                <code class={refCode}>{p.pattern}</code>
              </td>
              <td class={refTd}>
                <code class={refCode}>{p.flags || '—'}</code>
              </td>
              <td class={refTdMuted}>{p.description}</td>
            </tr>
          ))
        }
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <p class={css({ color: 'textMuted', fontSize: '0.88rem', mt: '1.5rem', lineHeight: 1.7 })}>
    Every pattern above is a reasonable, general-purpose heuristic, not an exhaustive spec-perfect grammar — the
    Base64 pattern, for instance, can't tell a genuine base64 blob from 32+ characters of coincidentally
    base64-alphabet text, and the registry-key pattern doesn't validate against the real hive/key namespace. Treat
    a match as a lead worth reviewing, not a guarantee.
  </p>

  <h2 id="related" class={sectionH2}>
    <Icon name="wrench" size={20} class={css({ color: 'primary' })} /> Related tools
  </h2>
  <div class={relatedList}>
    <div>
      <a href="/tools/deobfuscator/" class={toolChip}>
        <Icon name="key" size={13} /> Deobfuscation Recipe Builder <Icon name="arrow-right" size={13} />
      </a>
      <p class={relatedReason}>Working with an obfuscated blob? Peel it back here before you go pattern-hunting.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <a href="/tools/ioc-extractor/" class={toolChip}>
        <Icon name="search" size={13} /> IOC Extractor <Icon name="arrow-right" size={13} />
      </a>
      <p class={relatedReason}>
        Need a fixed set of IOC categories (IPs, hashes, CVEs, ATT&amp;CK IDs) extracted in one pass instead of a
        hand-written pattern? Use the IOC Extractor.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <a href="/tools/sigma-tester/" class={toolChip}>
        <Icon name="target" size={13} /> Sigma Rule Tester <Icon name="arrow-right" size={13} />
      </a>
      <p class={relatedReason}>
        Once a pattern is solid, drop it straight into a Sigma rule's |re modifier and test it live against
        sample events.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
